markets.title: Will **Florida** average less than 10,000 new COVID-19 cases per day by March?
markets.subtitle: <10K
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for Florida is below 10,000 for a single day between Issuance and March 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for March 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on March 08, 2022.

markets.title: Will **Florida average more than 100,000 new COVID-19 cases** per day by February 1?
markets.subtitle: >100K
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for Florida is above 100,000 for a single day between Issuance and February 01, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for February 01, 2022, or 10:00 AM on February 04, 2022.

markets.title: Will **Florida** have peak new average COVID-19 cases by the end of the year?
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for Florida is above 21,640 for a single day between Issuance and December 31, 2021, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occured, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for December 31, 2021, or 10:00 AM on January 07, 2022.
